== News
- \[01-10-2024\] I am teaching EECS 492 - Introduction to Artificial Intelligence again as a Graduate Student Instructor (GSI) in Winter 2024 at UMich.
- \[10-07-2023\] One paper accepted to EMNLP 2023 Main Conference.
- \[08-29-2023\] I am teaching EECS 492 - Introduction to Artificial Intelligence as a Graduate Student Instructor (GSI) in Fall 2023 at UMich.

== About me
My name is Zheyuan (Brian) Zhang (张喆元 in chinese). I am a master student at the [https://umich.edu/ University of Michigan] pursuing Robotics MS in the [https://robotics.umich.edu/ Robotics Institute] and Cognitive Science Graduate Certificate in the [https://lsa.umich.edu/weinberginstitute Weinberg Institute for Cognitive Science]. Currently, I am a research assistant at the [https://sled.eecs.umich.edu/ Situated Language and Embodied Dialogue (SLED)] lab, advised by Professor [https://web.eecs.umich.edu/~chaijy/ Joyce Chai]. I am also fortunate to work with Professor [https://web.eecs.umich.edu/~honglak/ Honglak Lee] and Professor [https://people.csail.mit.edu/ganchuang/ Chuang Gan]. Prior to UMich, I received my undergraduate degree in Computer Science (B.S.) from [https://www.umass.edu/ UMass Amherst], [https://www.cics.umass.edu/ College of Information & Computer Sciences].

== Research
My research is centered at the intersection of artificial intelligence and cognitive science. Currently, I am particularly interested in Deep Learning, Natural Language Processing, Robotics, Cognitive Science: \n
- Deep Learning: biologically-inspired neural architectures and learning algorithms for online, continual and few-shot learning, compositionality, interpretability, explainable AI
- Natural Language Processing: human-like reasoning and planning, language grounding to vision and robotics, language acquisition, language emergence
- Robotics: embodied intelligence, robot learning
- Cognitive Science: cognitive psychology, neuroscience

